# CodeLens Feature Demo
#
# This file demonstrates the CodeLens feature for REST Client.
# You should see a clickable "▶ Send Request" lens above each HTTP request.

### Basic Request

GET https://api.github.com/zen

### Named Request

# @name GetGitHubUser
GET https://api.github.com/users/octocat
Accept: application/json

### Multiple Requests Without Delimiter

# These two requests will each have their own CodeLens
# even though there's no ### delimiter between them

# @name SearchRepositories
GET https://api.github.com/search/repositories?q=rest+client&sort=stars
Accept: application/json

# @name GetRepository
GET https://api.github.com/repos/octocat/hello-world
Accept: application/json

### Request with Headers and Body

# @name CreateGist
POST https://api.github.com/gists
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "description": "Example gist created from REST Client",
  "public": true,
  "files": {
    "example.txt": {
      "content": "Hello from REST Client!"
    }
  }
}

### Section Organization

### Authentication Section

# @name Login
POST https://api.example.com/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "demo",
  "password": "demo123"
}

###

### User Management Section

# @name GetUserProfile
GET https://api.example.com/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

###

# @name UpdateUserProfile
PUT https://api.example.com/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Updated Name",
  "email": "newemail@example.com"
}

### Variables

@baseUrl = https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com
@userId = 1

###

# @name GetTodo
GET {{baseUrl}}/todos/{{userId}}

###

# @name CreateTodo
POST {{baseUrl}}/todos
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": 1,
  "title": "Test Todo",
  "completed": false
}

