### Advanced Features

# @name GraphQLQuery
POST https://api.github.com/graphql
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{githubToken}}

{
  "query": "{ viewer { login name } }"
}

###

# @name FileUpload
POST https://httpbin.org/post
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----FormBoundary

------FormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="test.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

File content here
------FormBoundary--

###

# @name RequestWithQueryParams
GET https://httpbin.org/get?param1=value1&param2=value2&search=rest+client
Accept: application/json

###

# @name ComplexHeaders
GET https://httpbin.org/headers
User-Agent: REST-Client/1.0
Accept: application/json
Accept-Language: en-US,en;q=0.9
Cache-Control: no-cache
X-Custom-Header: CustomValue
X-Request-ID: {{$guid}}

### Instructions

# 1. Click any "▶ Send Request" lens above a request to execute it
# 2. Named requests show their name in the CodeLens (e.g., "▶ Send Request: GetGitHubUser")
# 3. CodeLens updates automatically as you type
# 4. All HTTP methods (GET, POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE, HEAD, OPTIONS) are supported
# 5. Variables like {{baseUrl}} and {{userId}} are substituted before sending
# 6. Section headers (### Section Name) are treated as comments
# 7. Use standalone ### to separate requests
